            <subject>Re: Slide 21: Differentiating wrt a discrete variable</subject>
            <message>&lt;p&gt;This is not the issue, because we take u to be a continuous variable.  Recall that we do not discuss quantisation errors in this course.  We assume that there are no quantisation errors.  We said that if the quantisation error is large, go for a more bits in the A/D converter.  But the differentiation through the expectation operator is a problem!  It is only an approximation.  The correct answer is to use LQG, covered in Chapter 13.&lt;/p&gt;</message>
